<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1067312-in-the-chapter-titled-xvii-the-flight-i">In the chapter titled &quot;XVII. The Flight&quot; I could not wrap my mind around the idea of leaving ones children behind to hide in the attic for seven years. It is difficult to imagine the choices Harriet had to make throughout her life. For instance, she had an affair with Mr. Sands and had his children in hopes that it would get her away from Dr. Flint. What would you have done?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1067312'><a id="like_count_community_question_1067312" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1067312?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">2 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F152519.Incidents_in_the_Life_of_a_Slave_Girl">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
